DB:		-MySQL is provided from Oracle under dual licenses system:
		 http://www.mysql.de/about/legal/licensing/oem/
		-alternatives:
		 -Relational DBs:
		 	-Percona: (MySQL fork) Cloud computing, performance
		 	-MariaDB: (MySQL fork) MySQLfounded by Original MySQL main developers, open source,
			 pushing boundaries with the most advanced optimizer in MySQL space, 
			 integrating with NoSQL solutions with its Cassandra Storage Engine, 
			 additional db functions
		 	-ourDelta: (MySQL fork)
		 	-Drizzle: (MySQL fork)
		 -NoSQL DBs:
			-MongoDB: Agile and Scalable
			-Raik and Elrang: open source database that illustrates how to build large scale 
			 systems using Erlang/OTP

SQLApi:		-SQLAlchemy: SQLAlchemy is the Python SQL toolkit and Object Relational Mapper, 
		 can be used in Python3

Implementation:	-Python3

RESTful:	-CherryPy: A Minimalist Python Web Framework	
		-web.py: web framework for Python that is as simple as it is powerful.
		-Bottle: simple and lightweight WSGI micro web-framework for Python
		-Flask: microframework for Python based on Werkzeug, 
		 Jinja 2 and good intentions. It's BSD licensed.

Flask installation:
		-linux: sudo apt-get install python-flask
		-(recommended):
			-python-flask-autoindex: automatically generated index pages for Flask applications              
			-python-flask-babel: internationalization and localization support for Flask                 
			-python-flask-login: user session management for Flask                                       
			-python-flask-migrate: SQLAlchemy database migrations for Flask applications using Alembic     
			-python-flask-openid: OpenID support for Flask applications                                   
			-python-flask-principal: identity management for Flask                                           
			-python-flask-script: set of utilities for use with the Flask framework                       
			-python-flask-silk: FamFamFam Silk icon set for Flask applications                          
			-python-flask-sqlalchemy: adds SQLAlchemy support to your Flask application                       
			-python-flaskext.wtf: Simple integration of Flask and WTForms           


eclipse UML plugin ( papyrus for eclipse-kepler)
		-update site: http://download.eclipse.org/modeling/mdt/papyrus/updates/releases/kepler



